Best of all are the rooms, which are all chic, stylish, luxurious and spacious.

I was able to resist the urge to leave the hotel for a couple of days, but eventually had to answer the siren call of the casbah, where I had my encounter with the slipper-seller.

As I climbed out of the taxi in Marrakech’s famously madcap main square, I found myself face to face with a baby goat. I had the perfect line ready.

‘Here’s looking at you, kid.’

